com.amplifyframework.analytics

Class AnalyticsProperties

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amplifyframework.analytics.AnalyticsProperties
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,AnalyticsPropertyBehavior<?>>>

    public final class AnalyticsProperties
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<java.util.Map.Entry<java.lang.String,AnalyticsPropertyBehavior<?>>>
    AnalyticsProperties provides key/value pairs to represent attributes of an AnalyticsEventBehavior. While different analytics services will have support for different datatypes, AnalyticsProperties provides a baseline of support for String, Boolean, Double, and Integer. If one of these aren't available in a given service, the plugin is expected to cast it to something supported. (e.g., convert Boolean true to the String "true") 
         AnalyticsProperties properties = AnalyticsProperties.builder()
          .add("PostType", "UserImage")
          .add("LikedUserID", 78219)
          .add("FirstLike", true)
          .build();
